### API POST /api/blog

This endpoint allows the client to create a new blog post.

#### Request Body

- raw (application/json)

    - title (string): The title of the blog post.

    - description (string): The description of the blog post.

    - tags (array): An array of tag IDs associated with the blog post.

    - categories (array): An array of category IDs associated with the blog post.


#### Response

The response is a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "success": {
    "type": "boolean"
  },
  "blog": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "id": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "title": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "description": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "slug": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "published": {
        "type": "boolean"
      },
      "publishedAt": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "date-time"
      },
      "author": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "username": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "email": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      },
      "tags": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "id": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "name": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "categories": {
        "type": "array",
